              "question_id": 1,
              "question": "Que1). \"The role of emotional intelligence in value formation is often overlooked.\" In this context, analyze the relationship between emotional intelligence and ethical decision-making. (8 marks)",
              "student_answer": "Value formation is a moral process not an emotional process, and is linked with family, education, upbringing, environment and society. But we cannot overlook the role of emotional intelligence in developing it.\n\nRole of emotional intelligence in value formation can be seen as-\n\n1. It helps in conflict resolution : Emotionally intelligent people manage their anger, frustration in peer pressure.\n\n2. Helps in ethical decision making :- Emotionally intelligent officer rather takes more stable decision than a normal person.\n\n3. Improves communication/ understanding problems.\n\nIt is overlooked because of the following reasons:-\n\n1. Society is more focus on money, fame and success.\n\n2. Moral values are only taught in text books, not practiced.\n\n3. Traditional practices are just for show off like for making reels, fb, instagram rather than learning why these traditions are designed to practice.\n\nHence emotional intelligence is a thin line in making a smart plus sensitive, high valued officer / human being. without emotional intelligence one cannot survive and tackle the challenges.",
