              "question": "Q:2 How can Swami Vivekananda's idea of 'service to humanity is service to God' be linked to the sense of responsibility in public servants? Explain with examples (8 marks)",
              "student_answer": "Swami Vivekanand believed that \"service to humanity is service to God\" which means as a bureaucrat one should consider should be giving service to people is as pure as giving service to God. We take this responsibility like we serve our God.\n\nSense of responsibility in public servants can be understood with following points:-\n\n1. Taking Duty as a sacred Job:- Public served don't see their duty like just a job.",
